{
  "texts": [
    "Different regions may have varying access to AI technologies, and cultural values may influence the perceptions of integrating and using AI in the medical setting.",
    "This variability could impact the universality of the proposed ethical framework and limit the applicability of teaching medical AI ethics as a part of medical education.",
    "Moreover, integrating new teaching content into medical curricula is challenging due to the need for time-intensive accreditation processes and extensive teaching content.",
    "The integration of new teaching content such as medical AI ethics education requires careful planning to ensure that future physicians are adequately prepared and not overwhelmed by information.",
    "In addition, limited access to instructors knowledgeable in ethics, medicine, and AI may pose a challenge to implementing the proposed teaching of medical AI ethics, as these experts may not be available in most institutions."
  ]
}